<TITLE> Fakhruddin leaves for China visit </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 15 (bdnews24.com) Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed flies to China in the early hours of Monday, to begin a four-day state visit. "The visit has both political and economic ramifications. Hopefully it will strengthen political ties and expand trade and investment relations," foreign adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury, who is accompanying the CA, told bdnews24.com Sunday. He said Beijing and Dhaka saw each other as "all weather friends", and the relationship was a fixture of Bangladesh's international relations. Fakhruddin is scheduled to hold talks with president Hu Jintao, vice president Xi Jinping, and prime minister Wen Jiabao, Iftekhar said The CA is expected to return home on the morning of Sept 19. The chief adviser and his entourage leave for the Chinese capital on a Dragon Airways flight shortly before 2am Monday, officials said. The chief adviser's wife Nina Ahmed, office secretary Kazi Md Aminul Islam and press secretary Fahim Munaim are accompanying the chief adviser. bdn
